# AXIONAX BACKEND — Core Universe

This repo is `axionax-core-universe`: Rust blockchain core + Python DeAI + ops + tools.  
**Version:** Core v1.9.0 | Tests: 201/201 | Chain ID: 86137 (testnet)

## Repository Layout

```
axionax-core-universe/
├── core/                  ← Rust Cargo workspace (core/Cargo.toml)
│   ├── core/<crate>/      ← 18 Rust crates (consensus, blockchain, node, rpc, ...)
│   ├── bridge/rust-python/← PyO3 FFI
│   ├── tools/faucet/      ← Testnet faucet
│   └── deai/              ← Python worker layer
├── configs/               ← TOML configs (monolith_*.toml)
├── ops/deploy/            ← Docker Compose environments
├── ops/scripts/           ← Monitoring scripts (Python)
└── scripts/               ← Node operation scripts
```

## Rust — Commands (always run from `core/`)

```bash
cargo build --release
cargo test --workspace           # must pass — 201/201
cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings   # zero warnings
cargo fmt --all
cargo audit                      # security check
```

- Workspace root is `core/Cargo.toml` — never restructure without direction
- All crates live under `core/core/` (exception: `bridge/`, `tools/`)
- See `rust-core.mdc` for deep Rust rules

## Python DeAI — Commands (run from `core/deai/`)

```bash
python -m pytest . -v --tb=short --ignore=tests
python core/deai/worker_node.py                                    # general worker
python core/deai/worker_node.py --config configs/monolith_scout_single.toml  # Monolith
python hydra_manager.py                                             # HYDRA dual-core
```

- Python 3.10+ only
- Dependencies: `core/deai/requirements.txt`
- Config: `worker_config.toml` (override with `--config`)
- Secrets: `.env` (from `.env.example`) — **never commit `.env` or `worker_key.json`**
- See `python-deai.mdc` for deep Python rules

